The subject is introducing the practical work in the radiological department. The students follow the choice, planning, performance of the investigation, the reconstruction process and archiving of the images performed by radiology technicians and radiologists. 
The student follows the radiologist on call consulting radiology technicians and planning and performing the radiological investigations in the emergency department.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1.	The aim of this subject is to obtain practical knowledge in radiology department: in x-ray, computed tomography, magnetic resonace tomography and ultrasonography aswell as in nucler medicine 2.	The aim of this subject is  to obtain the knowledge in planning, performing, reconstracting and archiving the investigations.  3.	The aim is to obtain knowledge in optimal planning of the radiological investigations based on radioprotection and patients situation in emegency department.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1.	The student understands what happens with the patients during the radiological investigations, how to prepare and perform the investigation and  to reconstract and archive the images.  2.	 The student understands the role of radiology technician and radiologists in the radiology department. 3.	The student understands the importance of the optimal planning of  investigations in different organ pathology dependant how most optimally and rapidly reach the diagnosis based on radioprotection, age and other risks.
